  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To examine whether daily oral zinc supplementation to HIV-infected Tanzanian preschool
      children reduces diarrheal and respiratory morbidity, delays HIV disease progression, and
      improves growth.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine whether daily oral zinc supplementation to
      HIV-infected Tanzanian preschool children reduces diarrheal and respiratory morbidity, delays
      HIV disease progression, and improves growth.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
